# tweet-delete product context

tweet-delete is a secure, theatrical app for deleting old public X posts. The utility is cleanup. The product is the ritual.

## Core product fantasy

The user enters a haunted low-fi DOS archive, walks through old public memory, collects posts into a burn bag, types a deletion poem, and closes the archive.

## Use these terms

- Command center, not dashboard
- Signal scan, not search
- Timeline descent, not reverse chronological browser
- Targeting rules, not filters
- Burn bag, not delete queue
- Clemency list, not exclusions
- Rehearsal, not dry run
- Deletion verse, not confirmation text
- Purge sequence, not delete job
- Black box report, not audit log
- Sever link, not disconnect account

## UX rules

- Queueing is safe.
- Sealing is serious.
- Deleting is irreversible.
- Always show account handle and post count before destructive action.
- Always distinguish simulation from live deletion.
- Always include pause and abort remaining during purge.
- Never use fake urgency.
- Never make destructive actions one-click.
